          "type": "text",
          "text": "That looks like **creeping buttercup** (*Ranunculus repens*) — note the three-lobed leaves with pale patches and the runners spreading along the ground. It's common in damp lawns. If you want it gone, dig out the runners before it flowers; mowing alone won't stop it.",
